---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const lastUpdated = "2026-04-10";
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms of Service | sen-ai.fr" description="Terms governing your use of sen-ai.fr — accounts, credits, acceptable use, AI output disclaimer, liability.">
  <Nav />
  <main class="pt-24 pb-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-charcoal">
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-charcoal-dark mb-2">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-charcoal-light mb-12">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal-dark mb-4">1. Acceptance</h2>
        <p class="text-charcoal-light leading-relaxed">
          By creating an account on sen-ai.fr ("the Service"), you agree to these Terms
          of Service and to our
          <a href="/privacy" class="text-coral hover:text-coral-dark">Privacy Policy</a>.
          If you do not agree, do not use the Service. The Service is operated by the
          entity listed on our
          <a href="/mentions-legales" class="text-coral hover:text-coral-dark">Legal Notice</a> page.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal-dark mb-4">2. The Service</h2>
        <p class="text-charcoal-light leading-relaxed">
          sen-ai.fr is a SaaS platform that helps you understand how generative AI models
          (such as ChatGPT and Gemini) reference your brand or domain. You enter a target
          domain, the platform pulls SEO data, generates personas and questions, queries
          one or more LLM providers on your behalf, and presents the results in
          dashboards and reports.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal-dark mb-4">3. Account registration</h2>
        <ul class="text-charcoal-light leading-relaxed list-disc pl-6">
          <li>You must be at least 16 years old.</li>
          <li>You must provide accurate and current information.</li>
          <li>You are responsible for keeping your password confidential and for all
              activity that occurs under your account.</li>
          <li>One natural person should not maintain multiple accounts to circumvent
              credit limits or rate-limiting.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal-dark mb-4">4. Credits and billing</h2>
        <p class="text-charcoal-light leading-relaxed">
          The Service operates on a one-time credit pack model. There is no
          subscription, no auto-renewal. Credits are purchased in packs via Stripe.
        </p>
        <ul class="text-charcoal-light leading-relaxed list-disc pl-6 mt-3">
          <li>
            <strong>Scan credits</strong> are consumed when you launch an AI scan
            (1 credit per question). Credits are debited at launch.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Content credits</strong> are consumed when you generate content
            artifacts (FAQ snippets, articles).
          </li>
          <li>
            New accounts receive a one-time bonus of 50 free scan credits to try the
            Service.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Refunds:</strong> if a scan fails (e.g. our worker crashes mid-execution),
            the credits debited are automatically refunded. Credits are not refundable
            once the scan has successfully completed and delivered results.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Expiration:</strong> credits do not expire as long as your account
            remains active.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Pricing:</strong> the credit pack catalog and prices are listed on the
            <a href="/pricing" class="text-coral hover:text-coral-dark">Pricing page</a>.
            We may change prices for future purchases; previously-purchased credits
            retain their value.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal-dark mb-4">5. Acceptable use</h2>
        <p class="text-charcoal-light leading-relaxed">
          You agree NOT to:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-charcoal-light leading-relaxed list-disc pl-6 mt-3">
          <li>Use the Service to violate any law, regulation, or third-party right.</li>
          <li>Submit content designed to extract personal data, harass, or defame.</li>
          <li>Reverse engineer, scrape, or attempt to bypass rate limits or credit gates.</li>
          <li>Resell or sublicense the Service to third parties without our written consent.</li>
          <li>Submit prompts intended to produce illegal, hateful, or sexually explicit
              content from the LLM providers we relay to.</li>
          <li>Use the Service in a way that disrupts or degrades it for other users.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-charcoal-light leading-relaxed mt-3">
          We may suspend or terminate accounts that violate these rules, with or without
          notice depending on severity.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal-dark mb-4">6. AI-generated content disclaimer</h2>
        <p class="text-charcoal-light leading-relaxed">
          The Service relays your queries to third-party LLM providers and presents
          their responses. These responses are statistical outputs from machine learning
          models. They may be inaccurate, incomplete, biased, or hallucinated. They are
          NOT legal, medical, financial, or professional advice. You are responsible
          for verifying any information before acting on it. We make no warranty as to
          the accuracy, completeness, or suitability of any AI-generated content.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal-dark mb-4">7. Intellectual property</h2>
        <p class="text-charcoal-light leading-relaxed">
          The Service software, design, and brand identity are owned by us. You retain
          ownership of the data you submit (target domains, brand information, custom
          personas) and of any content artifacts generated for your account. By using
          the Service, you grant us a limited license to process this data solely for
          the purpose of providing the Service to you.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal-dark mb-4">8. Termination</h2>
        <p class="text-charcoal-light leading-relaxed">
          You may terminate your account at any time from your settings or via
          <code class="text-coral">DELETE /api/auth/me</code>. Termination wipes your
          account, your solely-owned workspaces, and all the data they contain. Some
          billing records are retained for legal compliance (see Privacy Policy §6).
        </p>
        <p class="text-charcoal-light leading-relaxed mt-3">
          We may terminate or suspend your account for violation of these Terms or for
          extended inactivity. Where reasonably possible we will notify you in advance.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal-dark mb-4">9. Service availability</h2>
        <p class="text-charcoal-light leading-relaxed">
          We aim for high availability but do not guarantee uninterrupted service.
          Maintenance, third-party outages (LLM providers, Stripe, HaloScan), and
          unforeseen incidents can cause downtime. There is no SLA on the free or
          pay-as-you-go tiers.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal-dark mb-4">10. Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
        <p class="text-charcoal-light leading-relaxed">
          The Service is provided "as is" and "as available", without warranties of any
          kind, express or implied, including merchantability, fitness for a particular
          purpose, and non-infringement. We do not warrant that the Service will be
          error-free or that defects will be corrected.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal-dark mb-4">11. Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p class="text-charcoal-light leading-relaxed">
          To the maximum extent permitted by law, our total liability arising out of or
          relating to the Service is limited to the amount you have paid to us in the
          twelve months preceding the event giving rise to the claim. We are not liable
          for indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, or for
          loss of profits, revenue, data, or business opportunities.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal-dark mb-4">12. Governing law</h2>
        <p class="text-charcoal-light leading-relaxed">
          These Terms are governed by French law. Any dispute that cannot be resolved
          amicably will be submitted to the competent courts of France. If you are a
          consumer, mandatory consumer protection rules of your country of residence
          continue to apply.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal-dark mb-4">13. Changes to these Terms</h2>
        <p class="text-charcoal-light leading-relaxed">
          We may update these Terms over time. Material changes will be announced in-app
          and the "last updated" date will be revised. Continued use of the Service after
          a change constitutes acceptance.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal-dark mb-4">14. Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-charcoal-light leading-relaxed">
          For any question about these Terms:
          <a href="mailto:contact@sen-ai.fr" class="text-coral hover:text-coral-dark">contact@sen-ai.fr</a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <div class="mt-16">
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-coral hover:text-coral-dark font-medium transition-colors">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7" />
          </svg>
          Back to home
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
